                    <h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
                    <p><em>Last updated: 2/23/2026</em></p>
                    <h4>Overview</h4>
                    <p>Halcyon Home Manager is a free hobby application created for personal and community use. <strong>It is strictly client side.</strong> Your privacy is important, and this policy explains what information the app does — and does not — collect.</p>
                    <h4>Information We Collect</h4>
                    <p>This application does <strong>not collect, store, or transmit any personal data</strong>.</p>
                    <ul> <li>No personal information is collected.</li> <li>No data is sent to external servers.</li> <li>No analytics, tracking, or advertising tools are used.</li> <li>No internet connection is required for the app to function.</li> </ul>
                    <p>All data created within the app remains <strong>on your device only</strong>.</p>
                    <h4>Third‑Party Services</h4>
                    <p>The app does not integrate with any third‑party services.</p>
                    <p>However, Google Play and the Google Play Store app may collect diagnostic or usage data as part of their platform operations. This data collection is governed by Google’s own privacy policies.</p>
                    <h4>Data Storage</h4>
                    <p>All information you enter into the app is stored locally on your device. Deleting the app will remove all locally stored data.</p>
                    <h4>Children’s Privacy</h4>
                    <p>This app does not collect any personal information from users of any age, including children.</p>
                    <h4>Changes to This Policy</h4>
                    <p>If the app’s functionality changes in a way that affects privacy, this policy will be updated. The latest version will always be available on the Google Play Store listing.</p>
                    <h4>Contact</h4>
                    <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, you may contact the developer at his GitHub page:<br> <strong>https://github.com/Aaronkarr11</strong></p>
                    <p>You may also submit issues and or contribute. This application is open source.</p>

